<br>
MOB's have unique AI depending on their model.  I.e. animals in general usually tend to hit the player closest to it, even if that player is doing less damage.  Some mobs have very good AI, and are extremely difficult if not impossible to taunt off somebody doing even slightly more damage than you.  Some mobs will totally ignore your pet regardless of the personal damage you have/have not done to the mob, and come right for you - i.e. the reason the majority of mages prefer earth pets when soloing.<br>
<br>
At your level, especially fighting skeletons, your tactic is safe.  The skeleton does not regard YOU as the primary target needing to die - it regards your pet equally in it's hate.  So, it's content to let you nuke it for 80% damage, then beat senselessly on your pet because it's closer than you.  <br>
<br>
The only time mob's AI is over-written is when the player gets too low on life, usually 1 bub - then all mobs around you go into Kill mode - and will resist all taunts &amp; attacks from other players/pets until you are dead, or healed up over the &quot;Kill Zone&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utaoxektrickyhands.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TaoxekTrickyhands</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(6/1/01 7:47:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this a Strategy or just due to my level ?</span><hr size=1> Did someone say they summon mod rods as a weapons for their pet?<br>
